\[Jan 01, 2022\] [https://github.com/sun-umn/NCVX NCVX] with its initial solver *PyGRANSO* v1.0.0 released. Check the [https://ncvx.org/ documentation page] and [https://github.com/sun-umn/NCVX GitHub repo] for more information.

\[Nov 29, 2021\] Proud to release our paper [https://arxiv.org/abs/2111.13984 NCVX: A User-Friendly and Scalable Package for Nonconvex Optimization in Machine Learning] on arXiv! [https://ncvx.org/ NCVX] is the initial translation and revamping of the [http://www.timmitchell.com/software/GRANSO/ GRANSO package], with convenient features such as auto-differentiation and GPU support. In particular, NCVX can be used to solve constrained deep learning problems.

\[May 25, 2021\] I am funded by the [https://research.umn.edu/units/umii U of M Informatics Institute (UMII) Seed Grant Program] 
to revamp the [http://www.timmitchell.com/software/GRANSO/ GRANSO] package into a user-friendly, scalable numerical optimization package. 

